<p>Here is the first in a series of videos that explains it all: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XPPYaVcXo1I" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-comment','www.youtube.com']);" rel="nofollow">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XPPYaVcXo1I</a></p>
<p>The whole cholesterol = heart disease theory is based on unsound evidence! </p>
<p>As for dietary cholesterol, it has little or no effect on blood levels of the average person. There are some that are sensitive, but most of us, at most, will see a very slight change (2-5 points maybe) with a higher level of dietary cholesterol! </p>
<p>Also, read these articles about the original Framingham Heart study:<br />
<a href="http://www.proteinpower.com/drmike/cardiovascular-disease/framingham-follies/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-comment','www.proteinpower.com']);" rel="nofollow">http://www.proteinpower.com/drmike/cardiovascular-disease/framingham-follies/</a><br />
